n hyperelliptic surfaces and the study of covering maps of the Riemann sphere with a finite number of slits removed. This allows for the first book-length treatment of orthogonal polynomials for measures supported on a finite number of intervals on the real line. In addition to the Szego and Killip-Simon theorems for orthogonal polynomials on the unit circle (OPUC) and orthogonal polynomials on the real line (OPRL), Simon covers Toda lattices, the moment problem, and Jacobi operators on the Bethe lattice. Recent work on applications of universality of the CD kernel to obtain detailed asymptotics on the fine structure of the zeros is also included. The book places special emphasis on OPRL, which makes it the essential companion volume to the author's earlier books on OPUC.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aMATHEMATICSvCalculus. 0aMATHEMATICSxMathematical Analysis. 0aOrthogonal polynomials. 0aSCIENCEvPhysicsxMathematical &ampxComputational. 0aSpectral theory (Mathematics). 7aMATHEMATICS / Mathematical Analysis.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044250240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781400837052zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400837052423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400837052.jpg  a978-3-11-044250-2  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MTPY  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK